2465 ----
2466 APInt HexagonConstEvaluator::getCmpImm(unsigned Opc, unsigned OpX, 0
2467 const MachineOperand &MO) { ----
2468 bool Signed = false; 0
2469 switch (Opc) { 0
2470 case Hexagon::A4_cmpbgtui: // u7 0
2471 case Hexagon::A4_cmphgtui: // u7 ----
2472 break; 0
2473 case Hexagon::A4_cmpheqi: // s8 0
2474 case Hexagon::C4_cmpneqi: // s8 ----
2475 Signed = true; 0
2476 break; 0
2477 case Hexagon::A4_cmpbeqi: // u8 0
2478 break; 0
2479 case Hexagon::C2_cmpgtui: // u9 0
2480 case Hexagon::C4_cmplteui: // u9 ----
2481 break; 0
2482 case Hexagon::C2_cmpeqi: // s10 0
2483 case Hexagon::C2_cmpgti: // s10 ----
2484 case Hexagon::C4_cmpltei: // s10 ----
2485 Signed = true; 0
2486 break; 0
2487 case Hexagon::J4_cmpeqi_f_jumpnv_nt: // u5 0
2488 case Hexagon::J4_cmpeqi_f_jumpnv_t: // u5 ----
2489 case Hexagon::J4_cmpeqi_t_jumpnv_nt: // u5 ----
2490 case Hexagon::J4_cmpeqi_t_jumpnv_t: // u5 ----
2491 case Hexagon::J4_cmpgti_f_jumpnv_nt: // u5 ----
2492 case Hexagon::J4_cmpgti_f_jumpnv_t: // u5 ----
2493 case Hexagon::J4_cmpgti_t_jumpnv_nt: // u5 ----
2494 case Hexagon::J4_cmpgti_t_jumpnv_t: // u5 ----
2495 case Hexagon::J4_cmpgtui_f_jumpnv_nt: // u5 ----
2496 case Hexagon::J4_cmpgtui_f_jumpnv_t: // u5 ----
2497 case Hexagon::J4_cmpgtui_t_jumpnv_nt: // u5 ----
2498 case Hexagon::J4_cmpgtui_t_jumpnv_t: // u5 ----
2499 break; 0
2500 default: 0
2501 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled instruction"); 0
2502 break; ----
2503 } ----
2504 ----
2505 uint64_t Val = MO.getImm(); 0
2506 return APInt(32, Val, Signed); 0
2507 } ----
2508 ----
2509 void HexagonConstEvaluator::replaceWithNop(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
2510 MI.setDesc(HII.get(Hexagon::A2_nop)); 0
2511 while (MI.getNumOperands() > 0) 0
2512 MI.removeOperand(0); 0
2513 } 0
2514 ----
2515 bool HexagonConstEvaluator::evaluateHexRSEQ32(RegisterSubReg RL, RegisterSubReg RH, 0
2516 const CellMap &Inputs, LatticeCell &Result) { ----
2517 assert(Inputs.has(RL.Reg) && Inputs.has(RH.Reg)); 0
2518 LatticeCell LSL, LSH; 0
2519 if (!getCell(RL, Inputs, LSL) || !getCell(RH, Inputs, LSH)) 0
2520 return false; 0
2521 if (LSL.isProperty() || LSH.isProperty()) 0
2522 return false; 0
2523 ----
2524 unsigned LN = LSL.size(), HN = LSH.size(); 0
2525 SmallVector LoVs(LN), HiVs(HN); 0
2526 for (unsigned i = 0; i < LN; ++i) { 0
2527 bool Eval = constToInt(LSL.Values[i], LoVs[i]); 0
2528 if (!Eval) 0
2529 return false; 0
2530 assert(LoVs[i].getBitWidth() == 32); 0
2531 } ----
2532 for (unsigned i = 0; i < HN; ++i) { 0
2533 bool Eval = constToInt(LSH.Values[i], HiVs[i]); 0
2534 if (!Eval) 0
2535 return false; 0
2536 assert(HiVs[i].getBitWidth() == 32); 0
2537 } ----
2538 ----
2539 for (unsigned i = 0; i < HiVs.size(); ++i) { 0
2540 APInt HV = HiVs[i].zext(64) << 32; 0
2541 for (unsigned j = 0; j < LoVs.size(); ++j) { 0
2542 APInt LV = LoVs[j].zext(64); 0
2543 const Constant *C = intToConst(HV | LV); 0
2544 Result.add(C); 0
2545 if (Result.isBottom()) 0
2546 return false; 0
2547 } 0
2548 } 0
2549 return !Result.isBottom(); 0
2550 } 0
2551 ----
2552 bool HexagonConstEvaluator::evaluateHexCompare(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
2553 const CellMap &Inputs, CellMap &Outputs) { ----
2554 unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode(); 0
2555 bool Classic = false; 0
2556 switch (Opc) { 0
2557 case Hexagon::C2_cmpeq: 0
2558 case Hexagon::C2_cmpeqp: ----
2559 case Hexagon::C2_cmpgt: ----
2560 case Hexagon::C2_cmpgtp: ----
2561 case Hexagon::C2_cmpgtu: ----
2562 case Hexagon::C2_cmpgtup: ----
2563 case Hexagon::C2_cmpeqi: ----
2564 case Hexagon::C2_cmpgti: ----
2565 case Hexagon::C2_cmpgtui: ----
2566 // Classic compare: Dst0 = CMP Src1, Src2 ----
2567 Classic = true; 0
2568 break; 0
2569 default: 0
2570 // Not handling other compare instructions now. ----
2571 return false; 0
2572 } ----
2573 ----
2574 if (Classic) { 0
2575 const MachineOperand &Src1 = MI.getOperand(1); 0
2576 const MachineOperand &Src2 = MI.getOperand(2); 0
2577 ----
2578 bool Result; ----
2579 unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode(); 0
2580 bool Computed = evaluateHexCompare2(Opc, Src1, Src2, Inputs, Result); 0
2581 if (Computed) { 0
2582 // Only create a zero/non-zero cell. At this time there isn't really ----
2583 // much need for specific values. ----
2584 RegisterSubReg DefR(MI.getOperand(0)); 0
2585 LatticeCell L = Outputs.get(DefR.Reg); 0
2586 uint32_t P = Result ? ConstantProperties::NonZero 0
2587 : ConstantProperties::Zero; ----
2588 L.add(P); 0
2589 Outputs.update(DefR.Reg, L); 0
2590 return true; 0
2591 } ----
2592 } ----
2593 ----
2594 return false; 0
2595 } ----
2596 ----
2597 bool HexagonConstEvaluator::evaluateHexCompare2(unsigned Opc, 0
2598 const MachineOperand &Src1, const MachineOperand &Src2, ----
2599 const CellMap &Inputs, bool &Result) { ----
2600 uint32_t Cmp = getCmp(Opc); 0
2601 bool Reg1 = Src1.isReg(), Reg2 = Src2.isReg(); 0
2602 bool Imm1 = Src1.isImm(), Imm2 = Src2.isImm(); 0
2603 if (Reg1) { 0
2604 RegisterSubReg R1(Src1); 0
2605 if (Reg2) { 0
2606 RegisterSubReg R2(Src2); 0
2607 return evaluateCMPrr(Cmp, R1, R2, Inputs, Result); 0
2608 } else if (Imm2) { 0
2609 APInt A2 = getCmpImm(Opc, 2, Src2); 0
2610 return evaluateCMPri(Cmp, R1, A2, Inputs, Result); 0
2611 } 0
2612 } else if (Imm1) { 0
2613 APInt A1 = getCmpImm(Opc, 1, Src1); 0
2614 if (Reg2) { 0
2615 RegisterSubReg R2(Src2); 0
2616 uint32_t NegCmp = Comparison::negate(Cmp); 0
2617 return evaluateCMPri(NegCmp, R2, A1, Inputs, Result); 0
2618 } else if (Imm2) { 0
2619 APInt A2 = getCmpImm(Opc, 2, Src2); 0
2620 return evaluateCMPii(Cmp, A1, A2, Result); 0
2621 } 0
2622 } 0
2623 // Unknown kind of comparison. ----
2624 return false; 0
2625 } ----
2626 ----
2627 bool HexagonConstEvaluator::evaluateHexLogical(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
2628 const CellMap &Inputs, CellMap &Outputs) { ----
2629 unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode(); 0
2630 if (MI.getNumOperands() != 3) 0
2631 return false; 0
2632 const MachineOperand &Src1 = MI.getOperand(1); 0
2633 const MachineOperand &Src2 = MI.getOperand(2); 0
2634 RegisterSubReg R1(Src1); 0
2635 bool Eval = false; 0
2636 LatticeCell RC; 0
2637 switch (Opc) { 0
2638 default: 0
2639 return false; 0
2640 case Hexagon::A2_and: 0
2641 case Hexagon::A2_andp: ----
2642 Eval = evaluateANDrr(R1, RegisterSubReg(Src2), Inputs, RC); 0
2643 break; 0
2644 case Hexagon::A2_andir: { 0
2645 if (!Src2.isImm()) 0
2646 return false; 0
2647 APInt A(32, Src2.getImm(), true); 0
2648 Eval = evaluateANDri(R1, A, Inputs, RC); 0
2649 break; 0
2650 } 0
2651 case Hexagon::A2_or: 0
2652 case Hexagon::A2_orp: ----
2653 Eval = evaluateORrr(R1, RegisterSubReg(Src2), Inputs, RC); 0
2654 break; 0
2655 case Hexagon::A2_orir: { 0
2656 if (!Src2.isImm()) 0
2657 return false; 0
2658 APInt A(32, Src2.getImm(), true); 0
2659 Eval = evaluateORri(R1, A, Inputs, RC); 0
2660 break; 0
2661 } 0
2662 case Hexagon::A2_xor: 0
2663 case Hexagon::A2_xorp: ----
2664 Eval = evaluateXORrr(R1, RegisterSubReg(Src2), Inputs, RC); 0
2665 break; 0
2666 } ----
2667 if (Eval) { 0
2668 RegisterSubReg DefR(MI.getOperand(0)); 0
2669 Outputs.update(DefR.Reg, RC); 0
2670 } ----
2671 return Eval; 0
2672 } ----
2673 ----
2674 bool HexagonConstEvaluator::evaluateHexCondMove(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
2675 const CellMap &Inputs, CellMap &Outputs) { ----
2676 // Dst0 = Cond1 ? Src2 : Src3 ----
2677 RegisterSubReg CR(MI.getOperand(1)); 0
2678 assert(Inputs.has(CR.Reg)); 0
2679 LatticeCell LS; 0
2680 if (!getCell(CR, Inputs, LS)) 0
2681 return false; 0
2682 uint32_t Ps = LS.properties(); 0
2683 unsigned TakeOp; ----
2684 if (Ps & ConstantProperties::Zero) 0
2685 TakeOp = 3; 0
2686 else if (Ps & ConstantProperties::NonZero) 0
2687 TakeOp = 2; 0
2688 else ----
2689 return false; 0
2690 ----
2691 const MachineOperand &ValOp = MI.getOperand(TakeOp); 0
2692 RegisterSubReg DefR(MI.getOperand(0)); 0
2693 LatticeCell RC = Outputs.get(DefR.Reg); 0
2694 ----
2695 if (ValOp.isImm()) { 0
2696 int64_t V = ValOp.getImm(); 0
2697 unsigned W = getRegBitWidth(DefR.Reg); 0
2698 APInt A(W, V, true); 0
2699 const Constant *C = intToConst(A); 0
2700 RC.add(C); 0
2701 Outputs.update(DefR.Reg, RC); 0
2702 return true; 0
2703 } 0
2704 if (ValOp.isReg()) { 0
2705 RegisterSubReg R(ValOp); 0
2706 const LatticeCell &LR = Inputs.get(R.Reg); 0
2707 LatticeCell LSR; 0
2708 if (!evaluate(R, LR, LSR)) 0
2709 return false; 0
2710 RC.meet(LSR); 0
2711 Outputs.update(DefR.Reg, RC); 0
2712 return true; 0
2713 } ----
2714 return false; 0
2715 } ----
2716 ----
2717 bool HexagonConstEvaluator::evaluateHexExt(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
2718 const CellMap &Inputs, CellMap &Outputs) { ----
2719 // Dst0 = ext R1 ----
2720 RegisterSubReg R1(MI.getOperand(1)); 0
2721 assert(Inputs.has(R1.Reg)); 0
2722 ----
2723 unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode(); 0
2724 unsigned Bits; ----
2725 switch (Opc) { 0
2726 case Hexagon::A2_sxtb: 0
2727 case Hexagon::A2_zxtb: ----
2728 Bits = 8; 0
2729 break; 0
2730 case Hexagon::A2_sxth: 0
2731 case Hexagon::A2_zxth: ----
2732 Bits = 16; 0
2733 break; 0
2734 case Hexagon::A2_sxtw: 0
2735 Bits = 32; 0
2736 break; 0
2737 default: 0
2738 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled extension opcode"); 0
2739 } ----
2740 ----
2741 bool Signed = false; 0
2742 switch (Opc) { 0
2743 case Hexagon::A2_sxtb: 0
2744 case Hexagon::A2_sxth: ----
2745 case Hexagon::A2_sxtw: ----
2746 Signed = true; 0
2747 break; 0
2748 } ----
2749 ----
2750 RegisterSubReg DefR(MI.getOperand(0)); 0
2751 unsigned BW = getRegBitWidth(DefR.Reg); 0
2752 LatticeCell RC = Outputs.get(DefR.Reg); 0
2753 bool Eval = Signed ? evaluateSEXTr(R1, BW, Bits, Inputs, RC) 0
2754 : evaluateZEXTr(R1, BW, Bits, Inputs, RC); 0
2755 if (!Eval) 0
2756 return false; 0
2757 Outputs.update(DefR.Reg, RC); 0
2758 return true; 0
2759 } ----
2760 ----
2761 bool HexagonConstEvaluator::evaluateHexVector1(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
2762 const CellMap &Inputs, CellMap &Outputs) { ----
2763 // DefR = op R1 ----
2764 RegisterSubReg DefR(MI.getOperand(0)); 0
2765 RegisterSubReg R1(MI.getOperand(1)); 0
2766 assert(Inputs.has(R1.Reg)); 0
2767 LatticeCell RC = Outputs.get(DefR.Reg); 0
2768 bool Eval; ----
2769 ----
2770 unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode(); 0
2771 switch (Opc) { 0
2772 case Hexagon::S2_vsplatrb: 0
2773 // Rd = 4 times Rs:0..7 ----
2774 Eval = evaluateSplatr(R1, 8, 4, Inputs, RC); 0
2775 break; 0
2776 case Hexagon::S2_vsplatrh: 0
2777 // Rdd = 4 times Rs:0..15 ----
2778 Eval = evaluateSplatr(R1, 16, 4, Inputs, RC); 0
2779 break; 0
2780 default: 0
2781 return false; 0
2782 } ----
2783 ----
2784 if (!Eval) 0
2785 return false; 0
2786 Outputs.update(DefR.Reg, RC); 0
2787 return true; 0
2788 } ----
2789 ----
2790 bool HexagonConstEvaluator::rewriteHexConstDefs(MachineInstr &MI, 0
2791 const CellMap &Inputs, bool &AllDefs) { ----
2792 AllDefs = false; 0
2793 ----
2794 // Some diagnostics. ----
2795 // LLVM_DEBUG({...}) gets confused with all this code as an argument. ----
2796 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
2797 bool Debugging = DebugFlag && isCurrentDebugType(DEBUG_TYPE); 0
2798 if (Debugging) { 0
2799 bool Const = true, HasUse = false; 0
2800 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.operands()) { 0
2801 if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.isUse() || MO.isImplicit()) 0
2802 continue; 0
2803 RegisterSubReg R(MO); 0
2804 if (!R.Reg.isVirtual()) 0
2805 continue; 0
2806 HasUse = true; 0
2807 // PHIs can legitimately have "top" cells after propagation. ----
2808 if (!MI.isPHI() && !Inputs.has(R.Reg)) { 0
2809 dbgs() << "Top " << printReg(R.Reg, &HRI, R.SubReg) 0
2810 << " in MI: " << MI; 0
2811 continue; 0
2812 } ----
2813 const LatticeCell &L = Inputs.get(R.Reg); 0
2814 Const &= L.isSingle(); 0
2815 if (!Const) 0
2816 break; 0
2817 } ----
2818 if (HasUse && Const) { 0
2819 if (!MI.isCopy()) { 0
2820 dbgs() << "CONST: " << MI; 0
2821 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.operands()) { 0
2822 if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.isUse() || MO.isImplicit()) 0
2823 continue; 0
2824 Register R = MO.getReg(); 0
2825 dbgs() << printReg(R, &TRI) << ": " << Inputs.get(R) << "\n"; 0
2826 } ----
2827 } ----
2828 } ----
2829 } ----
2830 #endif ----
2831 ----
2832 // Avoid generating TFRIs for register transfers---this will keep the ----
2833 // coalescing opportunities. ----
2834 if (MI.isCopy()) 0
2835 return false; 0
2836 ----
2837 MachineFunction *MF = MI.getParent()->getParent(); 0
2838 auto &HST = MF->getSubtarget(); 0
2839 ----
2840 // Collect all virtual register-def operands. ----
2841 SmallVector DefRegs; 0
2842 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.operands()) { 0
2843 if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.isDef()) 0
2844 continue; 0
2845 Register R = MO.getReg(); 0
2846 if (!R.isVirtual()) 0
2847 continue; 0
2848 assert(!MO.getSubReg()); 0
2849 assert(Inputs.has(R)); 0
2850 DefRegs.push_back(R); 0
2851 } ----
2852 ----
2853 MachineBasicBlock &B = *MI.getParent(); 0
2854 const DebugLoc &DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
2855 unsigned ChangedNum = 0; 0
2856 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
2857 SmallVector NewInstrs; 0
2858 #endif ----
2859 ----
2860 // For each defined register, if it is a constant, create an instruction ----
2861 // NewR = const ----
2862 // and replace all uses of the defined register with NewR. ----
2863 for (unsigned i = 0, n = DefRegs.size(); i < n; ++i) { 0
2864 unsigned R = DefRegs[i]; 0
2865 const LatticeCell &L = Inputs.get(R); 0
2866 if (L.isBottom()) 0
2867 continue; 0
2868 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = MRI->getRegClass(R); 0
2869 MachineBasicBlock::iterator At = MI.getIterator(); 0
2870 ----
2871 if (!L.isSingle()) { 0
2872 // If this a zero/non-zero cell, we can fold a definition ----
2873 // of a predicate register. ----
2874 using P = ConstantProperties; ----
2875 ----
2876 uint64_t Ps = L.properties(); 0
2877 if (!(Ps & (P::Zero|P::NonZero))) 0
2878 continue; 0
2879 const TargetRegisterClass *PredRC = &Hexagon::PredRegsRegClass; 0
2880 if (RC != PredRC) 0
2881 continue; 0
2882 const MCInstrDesc *NewD = (Ps & P::Zero) ? 0
2883 &HII.get(Hexagon::PS_false) : 0
2884 &HII.get(Hexagon::PS_true); 0
2885 Register NewR = MRI->createVirtualRegister(PredRC); 0
2886 const MachineInstrBuilder &MIB = BuildMI(B, At, DL, *NewD, NewR); 0
2887 (void)MIB; ----
2888 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
2889 NewInstrs.push_back(&*MIB); 0
2890 #endif ----
2891 replaceAllRegUsesWith(R, NewR); 0
2892 } else { ----
2893 // This cell has a single value. ----
2894 APInt A; 0
2895 if (!constToInt(L.Value, A) || !A.isSignedIntN(64)) 0
2896 continue; 0
2897 const TargetRegisterClass *NewRC; ----
2898 const MCInstrDesc *NewD; ----
2899 ----
2900 unsigned W = getRegBitWidth(R); 0
2901 int64_t V = A.getSExtValue(); 0
2902 assert(W == 32 || W == 64); 0
2903 if (W == 32) 0
2904 NewRC = &Hexagon::IntRegsRegClass; 0
2905 else ----
2906 NewRC = &Hexagon::DoubleRegsRegClass; 0
2907 Register NewR = MRI->createVirtualRegister(NewRC); 0
2908 const MachineInstr *NewMI; ----
2909 ----
2910 if (W == 32) { 0
2911 NewD = &HII.get(Hexagon::A2_tfrsi); 0
2912 NewMI = BuildMI(B, At, DL, *NewD, NewR) 0
2913 .addImm(V); 0
2914 } else { ----
2915 if (A.isSignedIntN(8)) { 0
2916 NewD = &HII.get(Hexagon::A2_tfrpi); 0
2917 NewMI = BuildMI(B, At, DL, *NewD, NewR) 0
2918 .addImm(V); 0
2919 } else { ----
2920 int32_t Hi = V >> 32; 0
2921 int32_t Lo = V & 0xFFFFFFFFLL; 0
2922 if (isInt<8>(Hi) && isInt<8>(Lo)) { 0
2923 NewD = &HII.get(Hexagon::A2_combineii); 0
2924 NewMI = BuildMI(B, At, DL, *NewD, NewR) 0
2925 .addImm(Hi) 0
2926 .addImm(Lo); 0
2927 } else if (MF->getFunction().hasOptSize() || !HST.isTinyCore()) { 0
2928 // Disable CONST64 for tiny core since it takes a LD resource. ----
2929 NewD = &HII.get(Hexagon::CONST64); 0
2930 NewMI = BuildMI(B, At, DL, *NewD, NewR) 0
2931 .addImm(V); 0
2932 } else ----
2933 return false; 0
2934 } ----
2935 } ----
2936 (void)NewMI; ----
2937 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
2938 NewInstrs.push_back(NewMI); 0
2939 #endif ----
2940 replaceAllRegUsesWith(R, NewR); 0
2941 } 0
2942 ChangedNum++; 0
2943 } ----
2944 ----
2945 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
2946 if (!NewInstrs.empty()) { ----
2947 MachineFunction &MF = *MI.getParent()->getParent(); ----
2948 dbgs() << "In function: " << MF.getName() << "\n"; ----
2949 dbgs() << "Rewrite: for " << MI << " created " << *NewInstrs[0]; ----
2950 for (unsigned i = 1; i < NewInstrs.size(); ++i) ----
2951 dbgs() << " " << *NewInstrs[i]; ----
2952 } ----
2953 }); ----
2954 ----
2955 AllDefs = (ChangedNum == DefRegs.size()); 0
2956 return ChangedNum > 0; 0
2957 } 0
2958 ----
2959 bool HexagonConstEvaluator::rewriteHexConstUses(MachineInstr &MI, 0
2960 const CellMap &Inputs) { ----
2961 bool Changed = false; 0
2962 unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode(); 0
2963 MachineBasicBlock &B = *MI.getParent(); 0
2964 const DebugLoc &DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
2965 MachineBasicBlock::iterator At = MI.getIterator(); 0
2966 MachineInstr *NewMI = nullptr; 0
2967 ----
2968 switch (Opc) { 0
2969 case Hexagon::M2_maci: 0
2970 // Convert DefR += mpyi(R2, R3) ----
2971 // to DefR += mpyi(R, #imm), ----
2972 // or DefR -= mpyi(R, #imm). ----
2973 { ----
2974 RegisterSubReg DefR(MI.getOperand(0)); 0
2975 assert(!DefR.SubReg); 0
2976 RegisterSubReg R2(MI.getOperand(2)); 0
2977 RegisterSubReg R3(MI.getOperand(3)); 0
2978 assert(Inputs.has(R2.Reg) && Inputs.has(R3.Reg)); 0
2979 LatticeCell LS2, LS3; 0
2980 // It is enough to get one of the input cells, since we will only try ----
2981 // to replace one argument---whichever happens to be a single constant. ----
2982 bool HasC2 = getCell(R2, Inputs, LS2), HasC3 = getCell(R3, Inputs, LS3); 0
2983 if (!HasC2 && !HasC3) 0
2984 return false; 0
2985 bool Zero = ((HasC2 && (LS2.properties() & ConstantProperties::Zero)) || 0
2986 (HasC3 && (LS3.properties() & ConstantProperties::Zero))); 0
2987 // If one of the operands is zero, eliminate the multiplication. ----
2988 if (Zero) { 0
2989 // DefR == R1 (tied operands). ----
2990 MachineOperand &Acc = MI.getOperand(1); 0
2991 RegisterSubReg R1(Acc); 0
2992 unsigned NewR = R1.Reg; 0
2993 if (R1.SubReg) { 0
2994 // Generate COPY. FIXME: Replace with the register:subregister. ----
2995 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = MRI->getRegClass(DefR.Reg); 0
2996 NewR = MRI->createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
2997 NewMI = BuildMI(B, At, DL, HII.get(TargetOpcode::COPY), NewR) 0
2998 .addReg(R1.Reg, getRegState(Acc), R1.SubReg); 0
2999 } ----
3000 replaceAllRegUsesWith(DefR.Reg, NewR); 0
3001 MRI->clearKillFlags(NewR); 0
3002 Changed = true; 0
3003 break; 0
3004 } ----
3005 ----
3006 bool Swap = false; 0
3007 if (!LS3.isSingle()) { 0
3008 if (!LS2.isSingle()) 0
3009 return false; 0
3010 Swap = true; 0
3011 } ----
3012 const LatticeCell &LI = Swap ? LS2 : LS3; 0
3013 const MachineOperand &OpR2 = Swap ? MI.getOperand(3) 0
3014 : MI.getOperand(2); 0
3015 // LI is single here. ----
3016 APInt A; 0
3017 if (!constToInt(LI.Value, A) || !A.isSignedIntN(8)) 0
3018 return false; 0
3019 int64_t V = A.getSExtValue(); 0
3020 const MCInstrDesc &D = (V >= 0) ? HII.get(Hexagon::M2_macsip) 0
3021 : HII.get(Hexagon::M2_macsin); 0
3022 if (V < 0) 0
3023 V = -V; 0
3024 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = MRI->getRegClass(DefR.Reg); 0
3025 Register NewR = MRI->createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
3026 const MachineOperand &Src1 = MI.getOperand(1); 0
3027 NewMI = BuildMI(B, At, DL, D, NewR) 0
3028 .addReg(Src1.getReg(), getRegState(Src1), Src1.getSubReg()) 0
3029 .addReg(OpR2.getReg(), getRegState(OpR2), OpR2.getSubReg()) 0
3030 .addImm(V); 0
3031 replaceAllRegUsesWith(DefR.Reg, NewR); 0
3032 Changed = true; 0
3033 break; 0
3034 } 0
3035 ----
3036 case Hexagon::A2_and: 0
3037 { ----
3038 RegisterSubReg R1(MI.getOperand(1)); 0
3039 RegisterSubReg R2(MI.getOperand(2)); 0
3040 assert(Inputs.has(R1.Reg) && Inputs.has(R2.Reg)); 0
3041 LatticeCell LS1, LS2; 0
3042 unsigned CopyOf = 0; 0

3135 const CellMap &Inputs) { ----
